            <thetext>When using a qxh locator to find a widget in a nested qooxdoo application (e.g. a demo in the Demo Browser), the locator returns the correct DOM element, but getQxWidgetByLocator fails when calling qx.core.Widget.getWidgetByElement since qx refers to the outer application&#39;s global qx object.
This could be solved by having the method that processes the locator steps store a reference to the qx object of any  iframes it encounters.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
